description: As Harley Quinn and Poison Ivy make their way to Russia on their flying manta ray, they are blasted by a mysterious force in the sky!
name: The Death of Illusion Part 1 of 3

description:
King Vikramaditya is one of the giants of Indian history. Hundreds of stories have been woven around this wise and noble king and his wonderful throne. Here is one such story.

Long after King Vikramaditya had passed away, his throne fell into the hands of Raja Bhoj. So beautiful and famous was the thorne that Raja Bhoj wished to ascend it. But he was stopped half-way by Kirtimati, one of the carved statues that adorned the throne.

Kirtimati had a story to tell Raja Bhoj. A thrilling story of mystery and adventure and courage and determination of Vikramaditya.
name: The Gold Coins of Mahakali

description:
Once King Bhoj got the throne of king Vikramaditya. The throne had 32 statues on it.

When the king Bhoj prepared to sit on the throne, suddenly a statue named Leelavati appeared and narrated a strange tale to king Bhoj about the great qualities of king Vikramaditya.

Which is greater, man's destiny or man's work?

Both are incomplete whithout each other. Read The Magic Wand to know a story.
name: The Magic Wand
